The paper deals with the development of a robust and computationally efficient attention-based convolutional encoder-decoder network for segmenting all the eye regions. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and attention blocks for semantic segmentation of the key eye regions. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques and multi-scale supervision, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the challenges involved in eye segmentation, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a model for eye segmentation, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
